						<summary>

						<p>Slab setup near the Agasikaṭṭi.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Jagadēkamalla [Jayasiṁha II] 1022 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It states that during the reign of Chālukya Jagadēkamalla, his queen Mahādēvi installed the god Traipurushadēva at Baḷḷaniṭṭage and made a grant of land to the temple. It is said that the land so granted was earlier obtained from Lōkāditya who was administering the <hi rend="italic">manneya</hi> of Ayyaṇavāḍi-300. It is said that the queen was then camping at Purvvaravaḷḷi.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 944, Dundubhi, Chaitra, śu. 13 Thursday. It corresponds to 1022 A.D., March 18, Sunday.</p>						

						</summary>
